        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1517688103" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7618349359985781854">4.5 stars<br/><br/>everything hurts and i&apos;m crying<br/><br/>This book just makes you take 10 seats. It&apos;s a story I can&apos;t even fathom being in. It&apos;s like an actual dystopia. Everything was so outrageous and haunting that it was almost unbelievable. <br/><br/>What I found myself enjoying was not just Yeonmi finding physical freedom outside the borders of North Korea and the human trafficking industry, but the mental freedom of learning how to be opinionated and advocating for others&apos; rights. This book is so touching, but so sa</span>
  <span id="freeText7618349359985781854" style="display:none">4.5 stars<br /><br />everything hurts and i'm crying<br /><br />This book just makes you take 10 seats. It's a story I can't even fathom being in. It's like an actual dystopia. Everything was so outrageous and haunting that it was almost unbelievable. <br /><br />What I found myself enjoying was not just Yeonmi finding physical freedom outside the borders of North Korea and the human trafficking industry, but the mental freedom of learning how to be opinionated and advocating for others' rights. This book is so touching, but so sad.<br /><br />I took off half a star because although it was an interesting story, the writing wasn't particularly beautiful and flowing, it was just okay. Because of that, it took me a little bit longer to read because it takes longer to get into, but it's not like it's a major issue because after all, english is practically her third language.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7618349359985781854" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

